Variable:it is named memory location which can store value or data and it can change n number of tymes during Execution


VAriableType/DataType:2 types
  1.primitive         2.Non primitive or Referencetype or classtype
    *Byte                 *Array
    *short                *String or Any classtype
    *int
    *long
    *float
    *double
    *char
    *boolean



VAriables or Data member
*Variable Declaration:
   int a;

*VAriable Initialization:
   a=10;

*Variable Declaration with initialization:
  int a=10;

*Variable Utilization:
  System.out.println(a);

*VAriable Re-Initialization:
   int x=10;
       x=20;
  System.out.println(a);//20 is the ans


*copying the one variable from another variable:
    int x=10;
        y=x;
    System.out.println(x);//10
    System.out.println(y);//10


local Variables:Any variable is declared within the method 
class Sample{
public static void main(String[] args){
int a=10;
sop(a);
}
}


Gloal variables:Any variable is declared outside the method and inside the class
class Sample{
int a=10;
public static void main(String[] args){
sop(a);
}
}

